Mission: Chandrayaan2
Organization: ISRO
Chandrayaan-2 IIRS Spectral Curve Extraction
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Overview
This project processes Chandrayaan-2 Imaging Infrared Spectrometer (IIRS) calibrated data to extract and visualize spectral radiance curves from selected pixels.

The script reads:

.hdr metadata file

.qub hyperspectral cube file

It then constructs a 3D spectral cube (rows × columns × bands) and plots radiance vs wavelength for selected pixels.

The output is a spectral curve plot saved as PNG.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Dataset:
Sensor: Imaging Infrared Spectrometer (IIRS)
Mission: Chandrayaan-2
Agency: Indian Space Research Organisation
Spectral range (approx.):
0.8 µm – 5 µm
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Data format:
| File   | Description                                          |
| ------ | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| `.hdr` | Metadata describing cube dimensions                  |
| `.qub` | Binary hyperspectral cube containing radiance values |

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Features

-Reads IIRS hyperspectral cube

-Extracts spectral signatures

-Handles negative radiance filtering

-Generates spectral radiance plots

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Requirements

Python libraries required:
-numpy
-matplotlib

Saves high-resolution PNG output
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
